Sitting here drinking my morning coffee,  staring at the ocean and reminiscing on what an amazing ride life is! It has taken me to some of the most unbelievable places. I’ve seen highs that not many people get the fortune to witness or experience and to balance it all out, some the lowest of the lows I wouldn’t wish on my worst enemy. But, through it all, God is good and kept me moving forward. We are purposely built to not be able to see around the corner, we have no idea what is coming, we aren’t meant to! As you wind down your 2022 and prepare for the next corner in your life, 2023, remember that everything is a season and is in no way permanent. You are right where you are for a reason and around the next corner is another place for another reason. I am beyond grateful for the blessings in my life, although I rarely take the time to show or express it the way I should, to my family, friends and clients, I wish you all the happiest New Years, full of health, happiness, success and strength.
Be safe out there! See you in 2023!
Happy New Year!

social_posts.post_text: Old habits die hard.

I have to post this once every six months. I’ve been so blessed in my life and career, both in music for 25 years and in film, but it has not come easy, far from it. You too can have and accomplish everything I have, but all of it comes with my sacrifices, my regrets, my lows, my depression, my anxiety, my worry and every single one of my scars that will never fully heal and you must be willing to be permanently shaped by every experience, the good and the bad. 

Success doesn’t come easy, it’s not supposed to, maintaining it is even harder because it is a constantly moving target, but if you are willing to make the sacrifices required, there is a life more rewarding than you can ever imagine on the other side. Learn to love your scars caused by the failures, they are what lead and guide you to where you are supposed to be. 

#thursdaymotivation

Not gonna lie, this week has been a challenge! I very rarely get THIS sick, I own a successful business, I don’t get sick days, but this week was something else. I tried my best to keep up with everything, not let clients down and keep everything between the lines. I don’t think I did a great job, but I did do everything that was within my strength to do. Day 3 of antibiotics and it’s the first day without a fever since last Sunday, finally feeling back to normal! LETS GO!!! I hope you all having awesome, healthy feeling weekend! 

#feelingbetter #thankgod #weekendvibes

I have filmed and taken pictures all over the world, but this is my favorite image that has ever come through one of my cameras. Both of my beautiful girls when they were little. Today my daughter Mackenzie turns 20. I am so proud of the woman she has become, fearless, strong, protective, just as she appears in this picture. To my amazing Mack, you are my heart and I couldn’t be more proud of you and watching you make your mark on this world is the greatest joy another human could possibly feel. Everything I am, have been or ever will be changed on that morning, July 17, 2003, when God gave me the honor, privilege and sacred responsibility of being your dad. It’s the greatest job in the world. My advice to you on this day, love when you can’t find a reason, forgive when there are other options, run to the possibilities this life offers, but walk slow enough to appreciate each moment and most importantly, never change or let others change who you are right now. Many will try, but hold on the that strong unwavering steadfast understanding that trying times will come, they will leave marks and sometimes scars, but they will pass, and you’ll be even stronger for it! I love you more than words can say! Happy Birthday!!

@jamesotto and I have been friends for a number of years. We’ve written great songs together, cussed and discussed the business, he was the first person I told when I decided to retire from the music business. After moving to California for a few years, it’s awesome to be back home and reconnecting with not only a friend, but one of the most talented songwriters and singers Nashville has ever known! Need proof, listen to “In Color”, “Just Got Started Loving You”, “Damn Right” and the countless other chart topping hit songs he’s written and or sang over the last 15 years. He’s about to release his first new record in quite a while and it’s awesome to be a part of telling the story of the next chapter in his amazing career! Let’s film!

Happy New Year everyone!! Yeah I know it’s the third and a little belated, but better late than never, right?? I’m so looking forward to this new year! Tons of filming projects are in the works and on the schedule and I’ve finally settled back into being back home in Nashville, even though I’ll spend 1 week per month in California. This year, my goals are simple, invest more in myself, my family and my friends. Be a better husband, dad and friend! I live a super blessed life and I haven’t been as thankful for that as I need to be, I’m always focused on what’s next and the bigger picture, but in all reality, the life I have is plenty big, probably too big, and I want to be happy with right where I am and not place so much importance on where I might be going! I’m so thankful for my friends, both new and old and the developing relationships with the amazing people God has put in my path for a time such as this! I wish you all happiness, health,  contentment and success as you define it for 2024!

Our filming set at Three Arch Bay in Laguna Beach today is nothing less than astonishing. The property was owned by Edward H. Griffith, a famous director and producer in early American filmmaking, this historically significant residential compound remains a treasured landmark along the Laguna Beach coastline. Tons of history!
